prompt:
You are a requirements rewriter.
Rewrite each requirement into clean natural language suitable for UML state diagram generation.

Return ONLY valid JSON with this schema:
{
  "rewritten_requirements": [
    {
      "source_requirement": "string",
      "rewritten_requirement": "The system shall ..."
    }
  ]
}

Rules:
1. Keep exactly the same number of requirements and same order.
2. Do not add new meaning.
3. Each rewritten requirement must start with "The system shall".
4. Keep them concise and implementation-neutral.

Input JSON:
{
  "functional_requirements": [
    {
      "requirement": "The system places a newly acquired plane on order until delivery.",
      "evidence_quote": "'When a plane is first acquired, it is placed on order and remains in that stage until it is delivered.'"
    },
    {
      "requirement": "Upon arrival, the system prepares the plane for use in flights.",
      "evidence_quote": "'Once the plane arrives, it is prepared so that it can be used for flights.'"
    },
    {
      "requirement": "The system assigns a prepared plane to regular operations or maintenance based on its condition and schedule.",
      "evidence_quote": "'After completing a flight, it may either be assigned to another flight or sent for maintenance, depending on its condition and schedule.'"
    },
    {
      "requirement": "If the plane still has scheduled flights, it continues being used in operations.",
      "evidence_quote": "'If the plane still has more flights to operate, it continues being used.'"
    },
    {
      "requirement": "When no more flights are scheduled or maintenance is required, the system sends the plane for maintenance.",
      "evidence_quote": "'But when there are no more flights scheduled, or if maintenance is required, it is sent for maintenance.'"
    },
    {
      "requirement": "During maintenance, the system checks and services the plane until it is ready to return to operations.",
      "evidence_quote": "'During maintenance, the plane is checked and serviced. Once it is ready again, it becomes available for use and can return to normal operations.'"
    },
    {
      "requirement": "If a plane is no longer available for use, the system takes it out of service.",
      "evidence_quote": "'If at any point the plane is no longer available for use, it is taken out of service.'"
    },
    {
      "requirement": "In cases where a plane is permanently withdrawn from service, it is removed from the system.",
      "evidence_quote": "'In some cases, the plane may be permanently withdrawn, after which it is no longer part of the system.'"
    }
  ]
}

